      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KANENA PROVLIMA (7) did a good job for a last-start placing at Menangle and came from a similar barrier to this to win the last time he raced here, taking his record at this circuit and distance to two from three. He is well placed. LIGHT ME UP NZ (1) is racing well having finished about 1.5m off the winner in two starts here since winning at Penrith. Suited up in distance having recorded two wins and a placing in three tries at it here and should get every chance from the ace draw. DANCE WITH CARMER (3) drew wide and worked in the city last start but had strong Menangle form prior, winning from wider than this two back. MASTER CATCH (8) recovered form an early break to finish only 1.5m off the winner when runner-up here last week. Draws wide but is up to winning if he gets it right.",
